1. Requirements Analysis
Understanding the functional and non-functional requirements is pivotal in designing a system that meets user expectations and business goals.

1.1. Functional Requirements
User Registration and Authentication

Sign-up/Login via email, phone, or social media accounts.
Multi-factor authentication for enhanced security.
User Profiles

Detailed profiles with personal information, preferences, and photos.
Privacy settings to control profile visibility.
Search and Discovery

Advanced search filters based on various criteria (age, location, religion, etc.).
Suggestions and recommendations based on user behavior and preferences.
Matching and Communication

Compatibility algorithms to suggest potential matches.
Messaging system for users to communicate securely.
Subscription and Payments

Freemium model with premium features.
Secure payment gateway integration.
Notifications and Alerts

Real-time notifications for matches, messages, and updates.
Email and SMS alerts.
Administrative Dashboard

User management, content moderation, and analytics.
Mobile Support

Responsive web design or dedicated mobile applications for iOS and Android.
1.2. Non-Functional Requirements
Scalability

Handle billions of active users daily with varying load patterns.
Performance

Low latency responses for search, messaging, and other interactions.
Reliability and Availability

99.99% uptime with failover strategies.
Security

Data encryption, protection against common vulnerabilities (e.g., XSS, SQL Injection).
Compliance with data protection regulations (e.g., GDPR, CCPA).
Maintainability

Modular and clean codebase for easy updates and feature additions.
Monitoring and Logging

Real-time monitoring of system health and user activities.
Comprehensive logging for troubleshooting and auditing.
Global Accessibility

Fast access across different geographical regions.
